# config/ops-safe-allowlist.txt — USER-OWNED safe-command allowlist.
#
# Ships as .example. Copy to `config/ops-safe-allowlist.txt` and edit
# to enable. The pack itself ships ZERO opinionated commands — this
# .example file is a starting point you own and tune.
#
# How it's used:
#   - Layer 1 of hooks/ops-risk-triage.sh checks each Bash command's
#     first one, two, or three tokens against the entries below.
#   - A command "fast-paths" (no AI call, no prompt) ONLY when:
#       (a) its name (1/2/3 tokens) appears in this file, AND
#       (b) its syntax shape is safe (no `>`, `>>`, `<`, `|`, `&&`,
#           `||`, `;`, `$()`, backticks, `<()`, `>()`, sudo, or a
#           secret-like path: .env, *.pem, *.key, *secret*,
#           *credential*, id_rsa, .aws, .kube/config).
#   - Commands that name-match but fail the shape check (e.g.
#     `pwd > leak.txt` or `cat .env`) fall through to Layer 2 (LLM
#     classifier) and will be classified there.
#
# Format:
#   - One entry per line. Whitespace-trimmed. Literal string match
#     (NOT regex).
#   - Comments start with `#`. Blank lines ignored.
#   - For multi-token commands like `git status`, write the full
#     name verbatim. The matcher checks 1/2/3 token prefixes; the
#     longest match wins.
#
# Tuning advice:
#   - START NARROW. Anything you add here can fast-path with no
#     review. If you're unsure, leave it off and let Layer 2 handle
#     it.
#   - Add aggressively only AFTER reviewing your `.tdd/ops-triage/
#     observe.log` and seeing that the same trivially-safe command
#     pattern keeps showing up.
#   - DO NOT add anything that writes/moves/deletes files, restarts
#     services, or touches the network. Those need at least Layer 2.

# --- Basic read-only POSIX shell ---
pwd
ls
cat
head
tail
wc
file
stat
echo
which
type
env
date
whoami
hostname
uname
df
du
true
false

# --- Git read-only ---
git status
git diff
git log
git show
git branch
git remote
git tag
git rev-parse
git config

# --- Docker read-only ---
docker ps
docker images
docker logs
docker inspect
docker version
docker info
docker compose ps
docker compose logs
docker compose config

# --- Kubernetes read-only ---
kubectl get
kubectl describe
kubectl logs
kubectl version
kubectl config

# --- Helm read-only ---
helm list
helm status
helm get
helm version

# --- Terraform read-only ---
terraform plan
terraform validate
terraform fmt
terraform version
terraform show

# --- Go toolchain (read-only / non-mutating subset) ---
go version
go env
go list
go vet
go fmt
gofmt
staticcheck
golangci-lint
govulncheck

# --- Standard build / introspection ---
make help
make list
